{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:first-timothy.2",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Timothy 2 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:1",
      "text": "I desire therefore, first of all, that supplications, prayers, intercessions and thanksgivings be made for all men:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:2",
      "text": "For kings and for all that are in high station: that we may lead a quiet and a peaceable life in all piety and chastity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:3",
      "text": "For this is good and acceptable in the sight of God our Saviour,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:4",
      "text": "Who will have all men to be saved and to come to the knowledge of the truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:5",
      "text": "For there is one God: and one mediator of God and men, the man Christ Jesus:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:6",
      "text": "Who gave himself a redemption for all, a testimony in due times.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:7",
      "text": "Whereunto I am appointed a preacher and an apostle (I say the truth, I lie not), a doctor of the Gentiles in faith and truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:8",
      "text": "I will therefore that men pray in every place, lifting up pure hands, without anger and contention.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:9",
      "text": "In like manner, women also in decent apparel: adorning themselves with modesty and sobriety, not with plaited hair, or gold, or pearls, or costly attire:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:10",
      "text": "But, as it becometh women professing godliness, with good works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:11",
      "text": "Let the woman learn in silence with all subjection.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:12",
      "text": "But I suffer not a woman to teach, nor to use authority over the man: but to be in silence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:13",
      "text": "For Adam was first formed; then Eve.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:14",
      "text": "And Adam was not seduced; but the woman, being seduced, was in the transgression.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.2.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:15",
      "text": "Yet she shall be saved through child bearing; if she continue in faith and love and sanctification with sobriety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
